comment: Really fun working on this one. Great tough hands and great tough feet.
Harder than some of the 8's here. subtle, beta intensive finish (unless you're really strong).
Nice to have a super crimpy, slabby route. Feels like hard climbing on granite. Harder than the tan V6.
So glad to finally figure out the top: great, creative problem. I bet the sport climbers figured this one out faster than the boulderers.
Fun holds, hard to hang on!
